<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-family: Arial"><FONT face="Franklin Gothic Medium"><FONT size=2>9. Analyze and resolve end user and system reported problems. Communicate problems and their resolution to the team. <o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-family: Arial"><FONT face="Franklin Gothic Medium"><FONT size=2>10. Follow and maintain policies and procedures to ensure system availability and keep each system tuned for optimum performance. Monitor the health of each database and the success of each backup. </FONT></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-family: Arial"><FONT face="Franklin Gothic Medium"><FONT style="BORDER-BOTTOM: 1px; BORDER-LEFT: 1px; BORDER-TOP: 1px; BORDER-RIGHT: 1px" size=2>11. Enforce standards â€“ documentation, data formats, naming conventions and change control. Follow standardized routine database maintenance procedures across all environments. <o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-family: Arial"><FONT face="Franklin Gothic Medium"><FONT size=2>12. Assist software engineers in query performance tuning as requested. Help identify inefficient queries; suggest alternatives in a constructive manner. <o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-family: Arial"><FONT face="Franklin Gothic Medium"><FONT size=2>13. Write PL/SQL packages and stored procedures as assigned. <o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></SPAN></P>
